Fig. 1
a, b and c, d shows the morphology of the as-prepared catalysts observed by TEM. The as-synthesized VCQDs and CQDs are of a spherical shape and have a uniform size of about 2.5 nm and 2.0 nm, respectively. Based on the atomic structural model [26] (Fig. 1e and f), the number of carbon atoms contained in a VCQD and CQD can be estimated to further calculate the turnover number (TON) and the turnover frequency (TOF) over VCQDs/C3N4 and CQDs/C3N4, respectively (Supplementary 1.3). The TEM image demonstrates that g-C3N4 is of an ultrathin sheet structure (Fig. 1g), corresponding to a high specific surface area (Table 1
). For CQDs(25 μL)/C3N4 and VCQDs(xμL)/C3N4 series catalysts, the dark-contrasted CQDs/VCQDs particles are unevenly distributed on the surface of g-C3N4 (Fig. 2
).
